by DHager at 2018-01-09T23:04:38Z

@bitgandtter When I look at `composer update`, I see a scriptable command-line cross-plaform package-management tool... From my perspective, all of that stuff is *supposed* to be safely-boring, perhaps with stodgy phrases like "POSIX compliant."

Ultimately, it means everybody has *more* time for fun, because they aren't debugging a mysterious crash or getting paged after-hours when something breaks.
